description:
&lt;p&gt;The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust (MYHT), in partnership with The University of Huddersfield has developed ground-breaking and exciting opportunities for Clinical Academic Research Nurses to join our Trust. Post holders will undertake a funded applied health sciences masters by research, alongside working in clinical practice within The Division of Medicine for Elderly Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Academic Research Nurse will provide leadership in the pursuit of innovative nursing practice and first class healthcare to strengthen the evidence base for professional practice at MYHT. The Clinical Academic Research Nurse role will be based at MYHT for 0.5 WTE (or equivalent) providing effective patient centred care and for 0.5 WTE at the University of Huddersfield.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Academic Research Nurse will be supported to engage in specified research activity and/ or research projects. This research activity will take place alongside studying towards a post graduate research degree (Masters or PhD).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enrolment onto a post graduate research degree at The University of Huddersfield will be January 2021. For course information see The University of Huddersfield website - post graduate health sciences MSc by Research. Entry requirement is an upper second honours degree (2.1) from a UK university or a qualification of an equivalent standard, in a discipline appropriate to that of the proposed programme to be followed. The successful applicant will have a minimum of 12 months post registration experience. This opportunity is a permanent band 5 position with a 2 years fixed term clinical academic research nurse appointment at The University of Huddersfield.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust (MYHT), in partnership with The University of Huddersfield invite compassionate, dynamic, innovative, highly motivated registered nurses to apply for this exciting clinical academic research nurse opportunity in the Division of Medicine for the Elderly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If shortlisted, and invited to interview, youwill be asked to present your research proposal along with a written research proposal submission.&lt;/p&gt;
